## How SELFISH we are. How VAIN we are.

1. The worldview values that a person develops at the age of 17 or 18 will almost undeniably carry through the code of conduct that guides him throughout his life.
2. Whether that principle is correct or wrong.
3. The parties will try to foreshadow and brainwash, understand and interpret the people and things they encounter.
4. Because this is what he knows what he believes.
5. It is nothing to do with right or wrong.
6. Something beyond his cognition? Denied.
7. The idea that there is almost no way to self-correct and identify with others is truly a tragedy.
8. He can only see what he can see.
  
<!--more-->


## DO NOT ATEEMPT TO CHANGE PEOPLE OTHERS.
That could be interpreted as a sign of danger or being controled.
If you must change someone, change your-self is better idea.


```
人有多自私 人有多虚荣
```
1. 一个人在十七八岁形成的世界观价值观几乎不可否认的会贯穿指导他一生的行为准则 
2. 无论这种准则是好是坏 
3. 当事人都会试图对其遇到的人和事进行铺垫与洗脑，理解和阐释，
4. 因为这是他的认知范围 这是他所相信的东西 
5. 正确与否不重要 
6. 超出认知之外的事物 
7. 一律加以远离与否定 
8. 几乎没有办法进行自我纠正与他人认同 这种思想真的是一种悲剧 
9. 你只能看到手电筒照到的地方 和夏天没有冰的地方
10. 不要试图改变别人 这会被解读成危险或者控制的信号 改变自己就好了
